ebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6a348733dda4d.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6a34873181093.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6a348730b8ec4.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6a348734167e2.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6a3487323e432.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6a3487342c182.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6a348732752b9.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6a3487316fcff.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6a348732937d5.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6a34872e57e97.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6a348733549ac.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6a34873392311.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6a34873380de4.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6a34873416212.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6a34873396c1e.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6a348734352d8.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6a348733df5a2.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6a34873416695.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6a3487340dc9b.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6a34873419b92.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6a3487341ab2d.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6a348734244f7.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6a3487341c277.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6a34873420c27.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6a3487341f8b1.jpg"/&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;h1&gt;&lt;b&gt;Description&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;This is a reshade mod that actually improves visuals, and actually works on switch emulators. Tested on Yuzu in Vulkan, untested in Ryujinx but should work if on Vulkan. It uses a "light" Ambient Occlusion effect to improve visuals, but without the aggressive flickering, ghosting, artifacts, and muddiness that the big heavy ones have when used with switch emulators (I believe its based on how they handle culling and depth, but I can't seem to get the other more polished AO effects to work on here. This was basically a "can it be done" kind of thing rather than a "perfectly polished beautiful game overhaul", so dont expect it to be anywhere near perfect lol. Its also a little performance intensive. I go from 60fps to around 45 in 1440p with an rtx 5060 and r7 5800xt, so don't use this expecting it to be easy to run just because I said it was "light". There is also a "Less Intense" Variant of both the regular and rainy presets that remove hdr and radiant global illumination, which greatly imprive visuals in the gerudo desert, but look slighly more like vanilla in others.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;TIP&lt;/b&gt;: This mod comes with 2 presets. One normal one, and one Rain one. The rain preset adds Screen Space Reflections (SSR), however, it applies these reflections everywhere. I totally reccomend it however whenever it is raining (hense the name), or when in zora's domain (massive overhaul feeling). Or use it all the time if you like it! If you want to quick switch between each one (so you never have to go into the reshade menu, then press the home key, navigate to the settings tab, and next to "Next Preset Key" select a key that does not conflict with others (I picked J). Additionally, next to "effect toggle key" you can select a key that turns reshade on and off (if you need an fps boost during a boss battle or if you want to compare visuals). I picked the "~" key.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;h1&gt;&lt;b&gt;Main features&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;Adds a light AO effect, bloom, fake hdr, global illumination, anti aliasing, and depth haze, without the fps drops and as intense flickering** that other presets have on switch emulators. ALL FOR FREE! No RTGI, no sketchy patreon, nothing.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;**As with all switch emulators, there will be some flickering from these affects, but I spent a lot of time tuning it specifically to lessen the intensity and frequency of the flickering (looking at you Revo). If you still see flickering after removing one of the culprits (Ambient occlusion, visible in the home tab of reshade as BETA AO), please let me know in the comments and I will do more testing to make it better. It's not perfect, it's not meant to be, but I'll try to make it playable unlike other switch reshade presets.&lt;br&gt;&lt;h1&gt;&lt;b&gt;Requirements&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;Just a working emulator with BOTW and reshade. Thats it&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
